{
 "name": "RPlog_Jedi_Lessons",
 "title": "Jedi Lessons",
 "summary": "On a moonlit beach near Coronet City, the Jedi Jessalyn Valios leads her student Orson Tighe through a night exercise in sensing the present through the Force, and he reaches out across the city and into his own past, recalling his childhood on Ukio and the family he left behind. The lesson drifts into an intimate, raw conversation about their losses -- Orson estranged children, Jessalyn orphaned past and the relationship with Simon that ended in rejection. Orson confesses his feelings for her, and the two wade into the cold surf wrestling with fear, the Dark Side, and self-doubt as Jessalyn struggles against her conviction that she cannot afford to feel. In the end she admits she cares for him but asks for time to heal, and it is her turn to walk away.",
